      <hedline>
        <hl1>Fashions of The Times</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Nadja Oertelt letter expresses shock at ad in Fashions of The Times special section (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>I was shocked and saddened by an advertisement in your fashion issue (Part 2, Fall 2000) for Perry Ellis that depicted a stunned woman lying disheveled on the floor as a naked man crouched over her. It was a horrible glamorization of rape and a perfect example of the fashion industry's willingness to go beyond the boundaries of good taste to sell clothing. This is not an ad for clothing; it is an ad for violence.</p>
        <p>Nadja Oertelt  Princeton, N.J.</p>
      </block>
